<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[Put the milk, butter, nutmeg in a large pot, season with salt, and bring to boil on low fire]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Slowly add the semolina, stirring vigorously to avoid lumps, then cook slowly for 10m]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Away from the fire mix in the egg yolks, parmesan cheese, butter. Spread mixture over greaseproof paper, put another sheet on top, and gently roll the mixture to 1 cm thickness]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Cool in the fridge for 30m]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Grease a baking dish, use a glass to cut disks from the mixture, place the disks in the baking dish slightly overlapping.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Scatter the fontina cheese, parmesan over the gnocchi and and bake at 200Â° for 20m]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
